value.value: The ridge that extends along the anterior margin of the netrion.
The sulcus that  anteriorly delimits the netrion.
The line that extends submedially along the mesoscutum and corresponds to the median border of the site of origin of the first mesopleuro-mesonotal muscle.
The suture that is located between the mesonotum and mesopleuron.
The area that is located dorsally on the thoracic segment and limited laterally by the pleuron.
The area that is raised and surrounds the propodeal foramen.
The area that is located on the cranium and is delimited anteriorly by the occipital suture and posteriorly by the postoccipital sutures.
The carina that surrounds dorsolaterally the occiput.
The fossa that articulates with the cranial condyle of the propleuron.
The depression that is located submedially on the occiput, ventral to the occipital carina.
The sulcus that is paired, extends dorsally from the posterior tentorial pit towards lateral ocellus and corresponds with the occipital ridge.
The area that is concave and surrounds the postocciput.
The apodeme that corresponds to the site of origin of the occlusor muscle of the thoracic spiracle.
The depression that extends along the lateral margin of a lateral ocellus or along anterior margin of the anterior ocellus.
The multi-tissue structure that is located on the top of the head, composed of the corneal lens, pigment cell, rhabdoms and synaptic plexus.
The anatomical line that is shortest and connects the compound eye and the lateral ocellus.
The sulcus that extends along the margin of compound eye and corresponds to the circumocular ridge.
One of the facets of the compound eye.
The sclerite that functions like a lid and covers the spiracular opening.
The foramen that is located anteriorly/ventrally on the cranium in which the mouthparts are positioned.
The sclerite that is located proximodorsally on the pretarsus and connects the distodorsal margin of the telotarsus with the dorsal part of the arolium.
The margin of the compound eye.
The band that extends along the medial margin of the eye.
The carina that is longitudinal and extends anteriorly on the lateral surface of the mandible.
The impression that extends dorsally of the condylar carina of the mandible.
The line that extends along the border between the eye and gena.
The anatomical space that receives sperm ejected from the aedeagus.
The anatomical cluster that is composed of the first valvulae, second valvulae, third valvulae, first valvifers, second valvifers and female T9.
The anatomical cluster that is composed of the third valvulae.
The sensillum with a paddle-shaped cuticular componenet on the probasitarsus.
The area that is located on the stipes and which articulates with the maxillary palp.
The anatomical cluster that is composed of the palpal segments.
The ridge that extends along the anterior margin of the metapectus.
The sulcus that corresponds to the paracoxal ridge.

The lobe that is connected to the distal margin of the prementum posteroproximally, to the premental hypopharynx proximolaterally and anteroproximally, to the glossa proximomedially and bears the basiparaglossal brush and the paraglossal sclerite.

The labial muscle that arises from the ventral part of the prementum, anterior to the origin of the premento-glossal muscle and ventral premento-salivarial muscle and inserts just distally of the distal margin of the prementum.
The projection that is located distolaterally on the hypostoma and extends to the clypeus separating the mandibular socket from the oral foramen.
The area that is located on the face and delimited ventromedially by the epistomal sulcus.
The carina that surrounds the compound eye.
The area that is located ventromedially on the paraocular area and is surrounded partly by the epistomal sulcus.
The area that is the dorsomedian part of the gonostipes and is the site of origin of the distodorsal and proximodorsal gonostyle/volsella complex-penisvalval muscles.
The area that is narrow and connects the parapenis with the rest of the gonostipes.
The signum that is located between the notaulus and the parascutal carina and corresponds to the site of origin of the dorsoventral indirect flight muscle.
The area that is delimited medially by the parapsidal line and laterally by the parascutal carina.
The area that is located on the upper face, is delimited medially by the antennal scrobe and laterally by the inner orbit.
The rim that extends along the lateral margin of the lateral area of the mesoscutum and delimits the preaxilla.
The projection that is lateral and located apically on the penisvalva.
The area that is lateral on the cranium between the frontal and occipital areas, separated above by the coronal suture.
The band that is located on the anterior part of the larval head.
The male genitalia muscle that arises from the proximal apex of the parossiculus and inserts medially on the penisvalva. The muscle inserts on the ergot if present.
